<p>Two things that might save you some confusion:</p>
<ol>
<li>It would be typical to split <code>IntakeCommand</code> into two files called, for example, <code>SetIntakeAlgaeSpeedCommand</code> and <code>SetIntakePositionCommand</code>. It can be confusing to others who read your code that a simple <code>1</code> or <code>2</code> is the difference between what you are setting and also what motor you are changing the behavior of. Generally it’s good if one command does one clear action.</li>
<li>Try to be more descriptive with variable names. This will be useful if other members of your team need to modify your code or if others need to help you. In <code>IntakeSubsystem</code>, for example, the motors are called <code>intake</code> and <code>algae</code>. It might be better to call the first <code>intakeMotor</code>, or even better <code>intakePivotMotor</code> or <code>intakeRollerMotor</code> or similar (I don’t know what your robot looks like).</li>
</ol>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-07-11T20:04:07.390Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":158,"readers_count":157,"score":46.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":504174,"topic_slug":"atualizando-a-programacao","display_username":"Karl Olson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36434,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Technical Mentor | 3476"},"post_url":"/t/atualizando-a-programacao/504174/2","custom_user_title":"Technical Mentor | 3476","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3679616,"name":"Murilo Miranda Santos","username":"murilo404","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/49beb7/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-07-11T21:03:31.686Z","cooked":"<p>thanks by your help</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-07-11T21:03:31.686Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":104,"readers_count":103,"score":30.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":504174,"topic_slug":"atualizando-a-programacao","display_username":"Murilo Miranda Santos","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":36434,"username":"olsonkarlp","name":"Karl Olson","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/b9bd4f/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":69705,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/atualizando-a-programacao/504174/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3679636,"name":null,"username":"NJ4611","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/71c47a/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-07-11T21:47:48.929Z","cooked":"<p>A small thing is that it looks like you are creating two instances of your intake and elevator subsystem, one in robot and another in robotContainer. I’m not too familiar with commands based, but I think you keep all your subsystem instances in robotContainer.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-07-11T21:47:48.929Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":89,"readers_count":88,"score":22.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":504174,"topic_slug":"atualizando-a-programacao","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":75029,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/atualizando-a-programacao/504174/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3679637,"name":"Murilo Miranda Santos","username":"murilo404","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/49beb7/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-07-11T21:55:10.272Z","cooked":"<p>This is because there are things that we did in our old way of programming, but we couldn’t put them as commands, like resetting our elevator encoder in teleopInit(), rotating the elevator when placing it in L1, etc… So, we put them separately</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-07-11T21:55:10.272Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":85,"readers_count":84,"score":32.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":504174,"topic_slug":"atualizando-a-programacao","display_username":"Murilo Miranda Santos","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":75029,"username":"NJ4611","name":null,"avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/71c47a/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":69705,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/atualizando-a-programacao/504174/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3679649,"name":"Karl Olson","username":"olsonkarlp","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/b9bd4f/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-07-11T22:05:15.478Z","cooked":"<p>To solve this issue, we put something like this in the ElevatorSubsystem</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public class ElevatorSubsytem extends SubsystemBase{
    private static ElevatorSubsystem elevator;
    public static ElevatorSubsystem getInstance() {
        if (elevator == null) {
            elevator = new ElevatorSubsystem();
        }
        return elevator;
    }
    ...
</code></pre>
<p>And use <code>ElevatorSubsytem.getInstance()</code> in <code>Robot</code> and <code>RobotContainer</code>. Then you can use it in both places but only one <code>ElevatorSubsystem</code> instance is ever created.</p>
<p>But I would suggest not doing this until you’ve thought deeply about if you <em>really</em> need the subsystems in both places. It may be dangerous or cause issues if you aren’t careful.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-07-11T22:10:39.739Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":76,"readers_count":75,"score":40.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":504174,"topic_slug":"atualizando-a-programacao","display_username":"Karl Olson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":69705,"username":"murilo404","name":"Murilo Miranda Santos","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/49beb7/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36434,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Technical Mentor | 3476"},"post_url":"/t/atualizando-a-programacao/504174/6","custom_user_title":"Technical Mentor | 3476","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3679650,"name":"Bryson Smith","username":"BrysonSmith","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/brysonsmith/{size}/227306_2.png","created_at":"2025-07-11T22:16:32.801Z","cooked":"<p>Alternatively to olsonkarlp’s solution, you could have a function of the Robot Container to reset the elevator’s intake and call that in teleopInit. For example:<br>
RobotContainer.java</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">// all of your code that is already in this file is above here
  public void resetElevatorEncoder() {
      elevatorSubsystem.encoder.reset();
      // this can also include the "subsytem.setPosition(Elevator.L1_POSITION);" that is found in Robot.java.
    }
} // End RobotContainer
</code></pre>
<p>Then, in your Robot.java</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">// All of your above code
  public void teleopInit() {
      if (m_autonomousCommand != null) {
        m_autonomousCommand.cancel();
      }
      // for this example, I did not modify the intake operations,
      // however, I would in a real codebase.
      intake.setPosition(Intake.ALGAE_POSITION);

     if (m_robotContainer != null) {
          m_robotContainer.resetElevator();
      }
  }
// All of your other code 
</code></pre>
<p>As I mentioned in the comments, it would be best to do the same thing for your intake instead of constructing a second instance of it in Robot.java. If you want an example for this, too, I’d be happy to write it.</p>
<p>I wrote this on <span class="abbreviation">CD<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chief Delphi"></template></span>, so if the code formatting is a little off or if there is a typo in the code, I’m sorry.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-07-11T22:16:32.801Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":66,"readers_count":65,"score":38.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":504174,"topic_slug":"atualizando-a-programacao","display_username":"Bryson Smith","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":69705,"username":"murilo404","name":"Murilo Miranda Santos","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/49beb7/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64015,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"9445 Software, Drive Team"},"post_url":"/t/atualizando-a-programacao/504174/7","custom_user_title":"9445 Software, Drive Team","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3679653,"name":"Murilo Miranda Santos","username":"murilo404","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/49beb7/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-07-11T22:17:04.337Z","cooked":"<p>I changed it as you put it in your answer. Can you see if I changed it correctly?</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-07-11T22: