":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":64015,"username":"BrysonSmith","name":"Bryson Smith","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/brysonsmith/{size}/227306_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36434,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Technical Mentor | 3476"},"post_url":"/t/atualizando-a-programacao/504174/9","custom_user_title":"Technical Mentor | 3476","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3679681,"name":"Karl Olson","username":"olsonkarlp","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/b9bd4f/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-07-11T22:27:03.350Z","cooked":"<p>You shouldn’t need a <code>new</code> in <code>ElevatorSubsytem subsytem = new ElevatorSubsytem().getIntance();</code>.</p>
<p>Also,</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public ElevatorSubsytem getIntance(){
            if( elevator == null){
                return new ElevatorSubsytem();
            }
            return elevator;
        }
</code></pre>
<p>As written, this will make a new elevator instance every time because you return the new subsystem without every setting <code>elevator</code>, so <code>elevator</code> will never be anything but <code>null</code>.</p>
<p>Because of these confusions, and possible problems depending on what you do inside <code>Robot</code> and <code>RobotContainer</code>,</p>
